{ The best move, with the idea to bring the king to h7 and get rid of the tactical problems. For example, after  17.Rc1  , I can finally put my knight on e4 with  17...Ne4  18.Qb4   @@StartBracket@@  18.Qd3  Bf5  19.g4  doesn't work because of  19...Nxf2  @@EndBracket@@  18...a5  19.Qb6  Kh7  20.O-O  Ra6  21.Qc7  , Finally my pieces are harmonious, and the d1-knight is still wedged in. I can do any moves such as  21...f5  or  21...Nd6  . This would have been a mature reaction, but I wouldn't have learned this valuable lesson if I didn't make this mistake! }
