9... Nxe5 10. d4
{ 10.f4  doesn't work as well in view of  10...Qb6+  11.Kh1  O-O  12.fxe5  Rfe8  when White is unable to properly defend  the pawn on e5. }
10... O-O 11. dxe5 Re8
{ Black tries to employ the same plan as in the @@StartFEN@@r2qk2r/pp3ppp/3b1n2/3pn3/6b1/3P2P1/PPP2PBP/RNB1QRK1 w kq - 0 10@@EndFEN@@  10.f4  variation, but the difference is visible in this position. }
12. Bf4
{ White can also play  12.f4  , but the text move invites Black to play a very natural move, which would be a mistake. }
12... Nh5 { Black takes the bait. } 13. Qd2 Bxe5 14. Bxe5 Rxe5 15. Qd4
