32. f5
{ Black has two ways to win: a human one and a machine-like continuation. I am wondering if you can find the latter... }
32... Qe7
{ 32...Ne5  33.Nb1  Rxe3  34.Qxe3  does win an exchange, but after  34...h6  Black's pieces are so powerful that White's position is practically lost. Possible ideas are ...Nf6, ...b5 followed by ...Bb6, while the bishop on a2 is doing nothing. }
