10. d5
{ By closing the center, White allows Black to reveal the point of playing @@StartFEN@@rnbq1rk1/ppp1ppbp/6p1/8/2BPP3/2P5/P3NPPP/R1BQK2R b KQ - 4 8@@EndFEN@@  8...Nc6  in the opening @@StartBracket@@instead of  8...c5  , which is far more logical@@EndBracket@@. What is Black's idea in this position? }
10... Na5
{ Black is trying to keep the c7-pawn in order to put the knight on c5. } 11.
Bd3 b6 { Preparing to reroute the knight. } 12. c4 Nb7 13. Ba3 Re8
{ What I will do next is exchange the bishops, after which the knight will be incredible on c5. It's a piece that cannot be driven out by pawns, so the c5- and d6-squares will be in Black's control. The queen and knight control the dark squares. }
