10... Re8 { A dubious idea and it is your turn to punish it now. } 11. Bxf7+
{ The most principled reply for White is the temporary piece sacrifice, after which it is not easy for Black to reach full equality.   Of course, there are many other options, like  11.Bd5  , but they're all imprecise.  11.Bxf7+  is a good move and the only one that refuted this line. }
11... Kxf7 12. Qb3+ Kf6
{ When I was playing this game, I was planning to rely on the text move because of the Topalov-Tukmakov encounter. Topalov lost with White after playing  13.f4  here. This is what I've expected, but, unfortunately, this line was later found to be completely unsound for Black. }
13. Rad1 { This is just winning on the spot because Black cannot do anything. }
13... exd4 14. Nxd4
{ The queen is so poorly placed that everything works for White. } *


