[FEN "r7/ppq2k1p/2p1r1p1/n1b1p3/Q1P1P3/2B5/P3NPPP/3R1RK1 b - - 0 19"]
[SetUp "1"]

19... b6
{ This position could have emerged from one of the lines that we discussed in the game's overview. Testing now your vigilance, as your task is to find a plan for White. }
20. Nc1 { En route to d3 and towards the e5-pawn. } 20... Nb7 21. Nd3
{ Black is searching for relief by trying to change the pawn structure. } 21...
Bd4 22. Bxd4 exd4 23. e5
{ The knight on d3 is doing a marvelous job as a blocker, but it also supports White's flank on the kingside. Black is condemned to a painful defense ahead. }
