12... c6
{ In the game, @@StartFEN@@r1bqr1k1/ppp2pbp/6p1/n2Pp3/4P3/B1PB4/P3NPPP/R2Q1RK1 b - - 2 12@@EndFEN@@  12...Bf8  was played. But how about the text move, what should White do? }
13. c4 b5 { Black is trying hard to challenge and destabilize White's center. }
14. c5
{ 14.cxb5  is less good in view of  14...cxd5  15.Qa4  d4  , which is a better version for Black compared to the main line. }
14... cxd5 15. Bxb5 d4 16. Qa4
{ The hasty  16.Bxe8  Qxe8  does win material but at a high price, as Black will get counterplay on the light squares. }
16... Re6 17. Bb4 a6 18. Bd3 Nc6 19. Bd2
{ Keeping an eye on the a5-square, to eliminate any ...Na5 ideas, while preparing Bc4 and, possibly, the Ne2-c1-d3 maneuver. White is better. }
*


[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "2) Establishing as a GM"]
[Black "Smbat Lputian vs. Levon Aronian â Puzzle #7"]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "r1b1rbk1/pp3p1p/6p1/q1pPp3/4P3/2PB4/P3NPPP/R2Q1RK1 w - - 0 15"]
[SetUp "1"]

15. a4
{ At this point, I thought that my opponent was a patzer. I have two bishops, and I can do anything I want. But then I started thinking about my position, and the deeper I was getting into it, the more I was understanding that I was the patzer and not my opponent. Should I have had a knight on d6 it would have allowed me to play for c4, but here, what is my plan?  This was a positional realization that, what was told in my childhood about having two bishops and having a great blockading piece, has nothing to do with reality. The reality is that White has better pieces while I will be passive. The c8-bishop doesn't have any squares, and ...f5 is not really an option.  And yet, never lose hope! Can you find a resource that I didn't? }
15... c4
{ Not allowing White to strengthen the center with c4 and seeking for immediate counterplay.   15...Bd6  is what I played in the game but after  16.Qc2  Rf8  ,  I was really depressed because I understood that I just got outplayed in the most primitive and simple way. My bishop on d6 is beautiful, but it's not doing anything. }
16. Bxc4 Bg4
{ Fighting for counterplay with ...Rec8 next, or perhaps ...Bxe2 followed by ...Qxc3. Black is still in business! }
*


[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
