[Round "?"]
[White "2) Establishing as a GM"]
[Black "Smbat Lputian vs. Levon Aronian â Puzzle #8"]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "r1b2rk1/pp3p1p/3b2p1/q1pPp3/P3P3/2PB4/2Q1NPPP/R4RK1 w - - 0 17"]
[SetUp "1"]

17. Kh1
{ White is not in a rush. He can always transfer the knight, so he plays a waiting move. That being said, better was @@StartFEN@@r1b2rk1/pp3p1p/3b2p1/q1pPp3/P3P3/2PB4/2Q1NPPP/R4RK1 w - - 0 17@@EndFEN@@  17.c4  f5  18.Nc3  since Black's attack is a lost motion while White's initiative on the queenside is more potent. How should Black react to White's prophylactic move? }
17... f5
{ This move shows my psychological situation. I should have probably played something like  17...Qc7  with the idea to play ...Qe7 and only then aim for ...f5. White is slightly better and can play something like  18.Bc4  Kg7  19.a5  and bring the rook to b1, but my position is kind of solid.  19...Qe7  Nothing tragic is happening, and White will probably play something like  20.Ng1  followed by Nf3 and Nd2.   Chessable note: perhaps the game still contains a lot of emotional load for Levon since his instincts were intact:  17...f5  is the best move in the position and the answer to this puzzle. Moreover, after  17...Qc7  , White can play the  18.c4  idea, with a slow but preferable game ahead. }
18. exf5 gxf5 19. f4 e4
{ After  20.Bc4  , the problem remains the same, I can never bring my bishop out because it will be exchanged. White has the simple plan to bring his  knight to e3. It will take a long time to bring the knight into play Ng3-f1-e3, but since I don't really have a direct plan, White can do whatever he wants.  If White's knight now stood on e3, his position would be excellent. Black must urgently create counterplay along the g- and h-files to prevent such a transfer.   Chessable note: Aronian is, of course, right regarding the urgency of Black's play, but the cold-blooded machines are more optimistic in evaluating this position. Black has ...Rf6-h6 and ...Bd7 ideas, with a position where the engines are happily stuck on 0.00. }
*


