[FEN "6rk/1p1b3p/p2b3r/q1pP1p2/P1B1pP2/2P3P1/R1Q2R1P/5N1K w - - 0 26"]
[SetUp "1"]

26. Rg2
{ It might look like Black has accomplished something because he at least now has some activity. But little has been achieved, as the knight is still coming to e3. Once the knight reaches this square, I cannot really untie myself because of the weakness of the f5-pawn. I somehow managed to make a draw by bluffing around.  Chessable note: White is better, but perhaps Aronian's evaluation is a bit harsh. Try to find the best defense for Black! }
26... Bf8
{ Rerouting the bishop to a more active square, from where it will keep an eye on the c3-pawn. The less accurate  26...Rh3  was played in the game. }
27. Ne3
{ In case of  27.Qb2  Bg7  28.Rc2  Rb6  29.Qc1  h5  followed by ...Rh6 and Black is still in the game. }
27... Bg7 28. Nd1 Be8
{ Reshuffling all the pieces would have been the way to keep fighting. } *


