{ What concrete idea do I have in mind here? } 15. Nc4 Rae8 16. g4
{ 16.Bg5  is perhaps possible, but I felt it was not achieving anything at the moment because I was not interested in exchanging the bishops after  16...Nd7  17.Bd2  . Here, I had to calculate stuff like  17...Kh8  18.Ne3  f5  19.Nxf5  g6  .  My point behind g4 is that I want to push the knight out with g5, and also more importantly I have a vicious trick in mind.   What is White threatening if Black plays a non-move like ...b6? }
16... b6 17. Nxe5 Qxe5 18. Bf4 { Trapping the queen! } 18... Bxe4 19. Qg3 Nh5
20. gxh5
{ Black's pieces are very uncomfortable. After  21...Qf5  22.h6!  , White is a lot better. }
