21... Qf6 { What did I play in the game? } 22. Bxe5 Qxe5 23. Ne3
{ The real problem with the e5-bishop disappearing is my e3-knight becoming a monster. You cannot touch it with pawns, you cannot touch it with the rooks, you cannot even touch it with the knight.In order for the knight to come and try to attack my e3-knight, Black needs to spend 5 moves @@StartBracket@@...Nc7-e8-d6-f5@@EndBracket@@, which is too much. The position is too open, and these weaknesses @@StartBracket@@the pawns on e4 and e6@@EndBracket@@ will not allow Black to do that. Therefore, White is already winning.   After a simple move like @@StartFEN@@3r1rk1/pb2q1pp/np2p3/4b3/1PP1p3/6PB/3BPPNP/2R1QRK1 w - - 7 20@@EndFEN@@  20.Rb1  , you can actually get such a nice position because once you address the main problem in the position, the weaknesses begin appearing and the position will collapse. }
