17... Qf7 { A strategic moment: what is the best continuation for White? } 18.
c5
{ White does keep some advantage.   Note that after  18.f3  e3  , the position becomes balanced.  For instance,  19.Qxe3  is well met by  19...dxc4  ,  when a beautiful spot on d5 is revealed for the c7-knight  . The other recapture @@StartFEN@@r1b2rk1/ppnn1qbp/2p5/3p1pB1/2PP3N/4pPPP/PP1QN1B1/R4RK1 w - - 0 19@@EndFEN@@  19.Bxe3  is also handing Black a lot of piece activity after  19...Nb6  followed by ...Nxc4.  Holding on to the pawn with  20.c5  would backfire. Following  20...Nc4  21.Qd3  Nxe3  22.Qxe3  f4!  23.Nxf4  Bh6  , Black's initiative is crushing. With the text move, White avoids those unnecessary complications. }
18... Ne6 19. Be3
