12... Qh5
{ Black's queen move supports both ...Bh3 and ...Bh6, and I remember I wanted to reply with @@StartFEN@@1rb2rk1/pp2ppbp/2np1np1/7q/2P5/1PN2NP1/PB2PPBP/R1Q2RK1 w - - 1 13@@EndFEN@@  13.Qg5  . However, had I thought a bit longer, probably I would have discovered an idea that is typical for White. I am not sure if you know it, but if you don't, then try to find it. }
13. h4 { Preventing Black's plans since ...Bh3 is no longer possible. } 13...
Bh6 14. Ng5
{ A very annoying move, almost trapping the queen, with a much better position for White. }
