17. Rb1
{ White wants to activate the c1-bishop, but Black has a strong way to prevent that from happening, otherwise, White will have to compromise the pawn structure. }
17... b5
{ Sokolov surprised me with this really good move. If we think about it, this is so strange. He has a hole on c6, and the pawn on b5 looks completely ridiculous. But, the pawns in the game of Chess have an extremely important quality: they can stop plans from happening. }
18. c4 bxc4 19. dxc4 Ne5
{ Now the bishop from b2 won't do any harm because the black knight will be fine on e5 and I will be saddled with a weakness on c4. }
