{ Find the easiest way to hold with Black. } 33... Qf6 34. Kf3
{ The idea is to seek counterplay after  34.e5  with  34...Qf5  .   In case of  34.Qd7  , Black can simply wait with  34...Bb2  since Kf3 is met by a check on c3, while  35.e5  is answered by  35...Qf5  . And if @@StartFEN@@8/3Q1pk1/1p3qp1/2p5/2B1PP2/6P1/Pb4K1/8 w - - 3 35@@EndFEN@@  35.Kh3  , Black has  35...g5  . }
34... g5
{ The pawn grab doesn't lead anywhere, but also  35.e5  is well met by  35...Qf5  , as we already know. }
