5. e6
{ Going for @@StartFEN@@6k1/3RK3/8/4P3/8/8/8/r7 w - - 0 1@@EndFEN@@  5.Ke8  is just wrong due to  5...Ra8+  6.Rd8  Ra6  and Black is already out of danger.  But the text move is also a bad idea. Why? }
5... Kg7 { A known way to defend. } 6. Ke8+
{ 6.Kd8+  Kf6  7.e7  Ra8+  8.Kc7  and now Black has  8...Ra7  , but also  8...Ke6  9.Rd8  Ra7+  , where White loses the pawn. }
6... Kf6 { Here comes the nice part. } 7. e7 Ke6
{ White's rook location is playing tricks on us. Had it been elsewhere to deliver a check, the position would have been winning for us. }
