[SetUp "1"]

1... Kf5
{ The immediate @@StartFEN@@5r2/8/6k1/8/1R6/1KP5/8/8 b - - 0 1@@EndFEN@@  1...Kf7  , trying to bring the king closer, fails to  2.Rf4+  and the pawn endgame is winning for White.  However, the text move is not a picnic either. Find the win for White. }
2. Rb6
{ White cuts the black king, which is also a known procedure to prevent Black from organizing the defense in a timely manner. }
2... Ke5 3. Kb4 Rc8 4. c4 { White will slowly promote the pawn. } 4... Kd4
